<topic id='business_definition_looked_after_child.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Looked after Child - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_looked_after_child">Looked After Child</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_looked_after_child">Looked After Child</xref>
 (also referred to as a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_looked_after_child">Child Looked After</xref>) is a child in the care of a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_local_authority">Local Authority</xref>
 either:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
through a Care Order made by a 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_court">Court</xref>
 or                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>voluntary agreement with their parent(s) to accommodate them.</p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>They may be looked after:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
in a 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_children_s_home">Children's Home</xref>,                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>by foster carers, or</p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>other family members.</p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
All 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_unaccompanied_asylum_seeking_child">Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Children</xref>
 are also 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_looked_after_child">Looked After Children</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
</body>
